properties.name: Boulder, CO- Naropa Institute
properties.description: Posted by Jmfernaboulder coWe visited the Naropa campus and got some literature about the college. I was interested in the study of Buddhism at the time and also in the Beat roots of the school esp the Jack Kerouac School of writing. Barry had lived here at one time. We had to go the mall to get him some new sunglasses b/c his blew off his face when he stuck his head out the window of the van. I don\'t remember why he did this but we had to stop the van so he could search for them. He was convinced that he saw them land in the grassy shoulder. Never found them.

properties.name: Rocky Mountain National Park
properties.description: Posted by Jmferna Rocky Mountain National ParkSpent the night on top of mountain in the van. I don\'t remember which one. There was still snow up there in June though. It was illegal because it was on an overlook and we didn\'t pay to camp in the park, just to drive through. It was windy. There were coyotes. We got a ticket. The next day we drove up above the treeline and hung out with the moose and lichen.
